    • requestContext

      default ContextMap requestContext()
      A request context associated with this GrpcMetadata that translates into HttpMetaData.context().

      Context can be used to associate a state with a request without serializing its state on the wire or transmit a state between HTTP and gRPC layers.

      Returns:
      a request context associated with this GrpcMetadata that translates into HttpMetaData.context().

    • responseContext

      default ContextMap responseContext()
      A response context associated with this GrpcMetadata that translates into HttpMetaData.context().

      Context can be used to associate a state with a response without serializing its state on the wire or transmit a state between HTTP and gRPC layers.

      Returns:
      a response context associated with this GrpcMetadata that translates into HttpMetaData.context().
